I have reviewed the `CONTEXT.md` and `CANDIDATE_BRIEF.md` materials and examined the currently leading models. 

To refine the currently best-performing `inner_loop_model`, I created a new `candidate.py` that builds on top of it by introducing a **lapse rate parameter (`epsilon`)**. 

The lapse rate is a heavily evidence-backed psychometric modeling strategy. It assumes that on a small fraction of trials ($\epsilon$), the participant guesses randomly (lapses in attention, motor error, etc.), which bounds the minimum probability of any choice to $\epsilon/2$. This allows the deterministic steepness parameter (`beta`) to tightly fit the bulk of the data without being artificially suppressed to accommodate a few outlier observations that heavily penalize the ELPD-LOO score.

